Kendall,

You can use the default parameter supplier, and supply each fish name
as a constant:

@DataPoint public static String ALBACORE = &quot;albacore&quot;;
@DataPoint public static String ZINGLE = &quot;zingle&quot;;

This gets tedious, so in 4.5 (I&#39;ll try to get a snapshot out soon), you can say:

@DataPoints public static String[] FISH = {&quot;albacore&quot;, &quot;alewife&quot;, ... }

or

@DataPoints public static String[] FISH = readFishFromDb();

Does that help?

   David Saff

